reviews.text: Without doubt the best Peking Duck I have tasted in Hong Kong! Their spin on the traditional sweet and sour pork was tremendous!

A high end Cantonese restaurant with high quality food. Very nice interior decoration, upmarket which is quite surprising since the restaurant’s location is fairly off from the prime commercial area & rather inconvenient. An undiscovered gem but going to cost you something for a nice meal. All of tonight’s dishes were superbly made with the exception of the vintage dish “good coin chicken 金錢雞”, which was fairly disappointing. I love this dish but very few restaurants are still making it & make it right nowadays.
Quality food and nice and quiet atmosphere.

Nothing special on the dim sum. Ample parking and a good atmosphere to have dim sum. Price is on the high side at least for my standard.

reviews.text: 清静环境優.中高價收费.特别餐卓擺設.食物上枱有觀感.每份食品份量少的式.非一般酒楼模式.招待有禮.7人结賬3千多元。
Without doubt the best Peking Duck I have tasted in Hong Kong! Their spin on the traditional sweet and sour pork was tremendous!
菜式细緻，地方寬敞，值得一去！

贵，但味道一般。服务态度一般至惡劣。
收一线的价钱，但五线质素。
叫一个㷛仔饭，竟要45分钟，谁愿意这样等。
純粹食裝修。

排骨㷛仔饭50分钟后终于来了。㷛呢？排骨呢？🙄
可以常到的粤菜馆！主厨虽年青 ，但认真。
